{"success": true, "message": "Fetched question.", "data": {"showTimer": true, "showAttemptInsight": true, "playSounds": true, "dontShowCorrectAnswerImmediately": false, "_id": "648b5a6e417cc3fb48d67f4a", "classes": [], "exams": ["615d76b2c52ffa3c944600df"], "subjects": ["615d708dbd4a37c4058ee5a8"], "chapters": ["615d6fed2b295b085ab6eba2"], "topics": [], "concepts": [], "previousYearPapers": [{"_id": "63f499891d196b49d9cd6b14", "title": "JEE Main 2023 (01 Feb Shift 2)", "isVisible": true}], "position": 0, "type": "singleCorrect", "level": 1, "approximateTimeRequired": 120, "question": {"text": "Two objects <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>a</mi><mi>n</mi><mi>d</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>B</mi></math> are placed at <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>15</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>and</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>25</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></math> from the pole in front of a concave mirror having radius of curvature <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>40</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></math>. The distance between images formed by the mirror is:", "image": null}, "options": [{"id": "DpqxS", "text": "<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>40</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></math>", "isCorrect": false, "image": null}, {"id": "X90Yx", "text": "<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>60</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></math>", "isCorrect": false, "image": null}, {"id": "G0MMI", "text": "<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>160</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></math>", "isCorrect": true, "image": null}, {"id": "tKsT1", "text": "<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>100</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></math>", "isCorrect": false, "image": null}], "correctValue": null, "solution": {"text": "<p>Let&#39;s consider the following diagram-</p><p><img src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/jee_main/685c633d-6f32-480f-a5d0-13db2fa8f1fa-9896603.png\" style=\"width: 350px; height: 225px;\" /></p><p>Let&#39;s assume that&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>v</mi><mi>A</mi></msub><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><msub><mi>v</mi><mi>B</mi></msub></math>&nbsp;indicates the distances of the images of objects A and B respectively.</p><p>Thus, by mirror formula, for object A, it can be written that</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtable columnspacing=\"0px\" columnalign=\"right center left\"><mtr><mtd><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>v</mi></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>u</mi></mfrac></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>f</mi></mfrac></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msub><mi>v</mi><mi>A</mi></msub></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>15</mn></mrow></mfrac></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>20</mn></mrow></mfenced></mfrac></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msub><mi>v</mi><mi>A</mi></msub></mfrac></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>20</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>15</mn></mfrac></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd/><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mfrac><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow><mn>60</mn></mfrac></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><msub><mi>v</mi><mi>A</mi></msub></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mn>60</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></mtd></mtr></mtable></math></p><p>Similarly, for object B, using mirror formula,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtable columnalign=\"right center left\" columnspacing=\"0px\"><mtr><mtd><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msub><mi>v</mi><mi>B</mi></msub></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>25</mn></mrow></mfenced></mfrac></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>20</mn></mrow></mfenced></mfrac></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msub><mi>v</mi><mi>B</mi></msub></mfrac></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mfrac><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mn>20</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>25</mn></mfrac></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mfrac><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow><mn>100</mn></mfrac></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mfrac><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mn>100</mn></mfrac></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><msub><mi>v</mi><mi>B</mi></msub></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>100</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>c</mi><mi>m</mi></mtd></mtr></mtable></math></p><p>Hence, the distance&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mi>d</mi></mfenced></math>&nbsp;between the images can be calculated as follows:</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtable columnalign=\"right center left\" columnspacing=\"0px\"><mtr><mtd><mi>d</mi></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mo>&#160;</mo><msub><mi>v</mi><mi>A</mi></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>v</mi><mi>B</mi></msub></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mo>&#160;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>60</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>100</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>160</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></mtd></mtr></mtable></math></p>", "image": null}, "videoSolution": null, "numericalUpperLimit": null, "numericalLowerLimit": null, "questionLabels": [], "__v": 0, "masterId": "MOGJMPYQ64235667", "bucket": "Easy Ques (Board Level)", "category": null, "microConcepts": [], "imageBaseUrl": null, "helperText": null, "isRemoved": false, "cpyqbSubjects": ["61bb58181213731910ea0b70", "61c055eae8ce0dc8a5c62d33", "616057750283de43c87e3e1b", "61964fe0a5a5260118868021", "61964f81a5a526011886801d", "629f39e4ac11b26562e0625b", "616057920283de43c87e3e1e", "615f0c729476412f48314dab", "61a8a2c2e8ce0dc8a5c62d2d", "629105adee9e3ae00d63352b", "629f385f263330a77be9fa7d", "616056cd0283de43c87e3e15", "616057190283de43c87e3e18", "62962075e7f8e9ac4daeafd7", "64d50bd73df7f4a7f3017f6f", "66b